    <string name="chat_avatar_content_description">FitZone Coach avatar</string>
    <string name="chat_bot_welcome">Hi! I am your FitZone Coach. Ask me about protein, workouts, water, BMI, or steps.</string>
    <string name="chat_reply_protein">For muscle gain, aim for around 1.6 to 2.2 grams of protein per kg of body weight daily.</string>
    <string name="chat_reply_water">A good target is around 2 to 3 liters of water per day, and more on workout days.</string>
    <string name="chat_reply_bmi">Use the BMI calculator with your height and weight. A BMI between 18.5 and 24.9 is considered normal.</string>
    <string name="chat_reply_weight_loss">For fat loss, keep a small calorie deficit, prioritize protein, and stay consistent with training and sleep.</string>
    <string name="chat_reply_workout">Start with 3 to 5 workouts per week. Focus on compound movements and progressive overload.</string>
    <string name="chat_reply_steps">A daily step goal of 8,000 to 10,000 is a solid range for general fitness.</string>
    <string name="chat_reply_default">I can help with workout plans, protein intake, hydration, steps, and BMI. Try asking one of those.</string>
    <string name="chat_reply_greeting">Hey! I can help with workouts, diet, sleep, hydration, fat loss, and muscle gain. What is your goal this week?</string>
    <string name="chat_reply_calories">For fat loss, start with a 300-500 kcal deficit. For muscle gain, start with a 150-300 kcal surplus and track weekly progress.</string>
    <string name="chat_reply_meal_timing">Aim for 3-5 balanced meals daily. Have carbs + protein 1-2 hours before training, and protein after training to support recovery.</string>
    <string name="chat_reply_recovery">Recovery matters: target 7-9 hours sleep, 1-2 lighter days weekly, enough water, and daily mobility to reduce soreness.</string>
    <string name="chat_reply_muscle_gain">For muscle gain: train each muscle 2x/week, progressively increase load/reps, and hit daily protein + small calorie surplus.</string>
    <string name="chat_reply_supplements">Helpful basics: creatine monohydrate (3-5g/day), whey protein to meet intake, omega-3, and vitamin D if needed.</string>
    <string name="chat_reply_injury">If you feel sharp pain, stop that movement. Use pain-free variations, reduce load, and consult a professional if pain persists.</string>
    <string name="chat_reply_motivation">Keep it simple: do a 10-minute start. Consistency beats intensity. Small daily wins build real long-term results.</string>
    <string name="chat_reply_thanks">You are welcome! Keep going - consistency is your superpower.</string>
